  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Collections.html

**Sort Colors problems approach in 3 steps**
## Approach
1. initalize low=0,mid=0 and high=nums.length-1;
1. check nums[mid] with nums[low] , also nums[mid] with nums[high] 
1. perform operation after comparison as show in switch cases.

```
class Solution {
    public void sortColors(int[] nums) {
        if(nums.length==1){
            return;
        }
        int low=0,mid=0,high=nums.length-1;
        while(mid&lt;=high){
            switch(nums[mid]){
                case 0:
                    int temp=nums[low];
                    nums[low]=nums[mid];
                    nums[mid]=temp;
                    mid++;
                    low++;
                    break;
                case 1:
                    mid++;
                    break;
                case 2:
                    int temp1=nums[mid];
                    nums[mid]=nums[high];
                    nums[high]=temp1;
                    high--;
                    break;
                    
            }
        }
    }
}
```

